Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel).

> TIP: You want the chunks to be small so they cook quickly.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Chop the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm pieces.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}, then pop half of them into a #bowl{}
and mash with a #fork{} until all broken up.

Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g} into small pieces. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Pop the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender and golden, ~{15-20%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and
cook until soft, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring frequently. Pour in half the @cider vinegar{15%ml},
stir, and let evaporate fully.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{1} and @tomato puree{30%g}, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the black beans (both whole and broken up), @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and
@water{150%ml}. Season with salt and pepper. Simmer gently until all the water has
evaporated, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Season with salt and pepper if needed.
Remove from the heat.

Mix the cooked sweet potatoes into the beans. Lay one of your @plain taco tortillas{6}
on the now-empty #baking tray{} and spoon some of the bean mixture onto one half of the
tortilla. Top with some feta and grated cheese. Fold the other side over so you have
a semi-circle. Press down to keep it together.

Repeat with the other tortillas - use three per person. Drizzle a little more @oil{} over
the top, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing) into a medium #bowl{}. Add the
remaining vinegar and season with salt and pepper, mixing well to combine.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{40%g} and tomato to the dressing and toss
well to coat.

Once the quesadillas are cooked, remove them from your oven and serve them on plates
(cut them in half before serving if you want). Serve the quesadillas with the salad
alongside. Enjoy!

> If you've added chorizo to your recipe, before you add your onion to your pan in the
> step above, add the chorizo and stir fry until it starts to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.
> Add the onion to the chorizo and continue with the recipe as instructed.

> Chorizo is optional - if using, add @?chorizo{60%g}(diced).